## Development Commands
```bash
# Install dependencies
pnpm install

# Run tests
pnpm test

# Build
pnpm build

# Development mode
pnpm dev

# Type checking
pnpm typecheck

# Linting
pnpm lint

# Format code
pnpm format
```

## Project Structure
- `src/` - Source code directory
  - `index.ts` - Main entry point
  - `lib/` - Library code
- `tests/` - Test files (use .test.mts extension)
- `package.json` - Package definition
- `tsconfig.json` - TypeScript configuration
- `eslint.config.mts` - ESLint configuration
- `devbox.json` - Development environment
- `.envrc` - Environment configuration

## Testing
Run all tests with coverage:
```bash
pnpm test:coverage
```

Run tests in watch mode:
```bash
pnpm test:watch
```

## TypeScript Standards
- Use explicit file extensions (.mts, .cts, .tsx)
- Use category-based path aliases (@/core/*, @/features/*, etc.)
- Follow ESLint configuration from @job-aide/tools-lint-eslint-config
- Use double quotes, 2-space indentation, semicolons
- Use kebab-case for filenames
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for type definitions
- Use `import type` for type-only imports

